</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,359,997]" pageId="1" pageNumber="540">
The new species 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stocchino" authorityYear="2018" box="[348,476,360,384]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Dugesiidae" genus="Dugesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tricladida" pageId="1" pageNumber="540" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="benazzii">
<emphasis box="[348,476,360,384]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="540">D. benazzii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Lepori, N. G." box="[689,847,359,384]" pageId="1" pageNumber="540" pagination="28 - 47" refId="ref7174" refString="Lepori, N. G. (1951) Sulle caratteristiche morfologiche e sulla posizione sistematica della planaria di Sardegna e Corsica gia ascritta a Dugesia gonocephala (Duges). Atti Societa Toscana di Scienze Naturali, 58, 28 - 47." type="journal article" year="1951">Lepori (1951)</bibRefCitation>
as a taxon endemic to the two islands Sardinia and 
<collectingCountry box="[151,240,396,421]" name="France" pageId="1" pageNumber="540">Corsica</collectingCountry>
. However, further studies carried out in the Tuscany Archipelago enlarged the geographic range of this species to include also Capraia Island (
<bibRefCitation author="Benazzi, M. &amp; Benazzi Lentati, G." box="[586,964,431,456]" pageId="1" pageNumber="540" pagination="1 - 182" refId="ref5860" refString="Benazzi, M. &amp; Benazzi Lentati, G. (1976) Platyhelminthes. In: John, B. (Ed.), Animal cytogenetics. Vol. 1. Gebruder Borntraeger, Berlin-Stuttgart, pp. 1 - 182." type="book chapter" year="1976">Benazzi &amp; Benazzi Lentati, 1976</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="540" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,359,997]" pageId="1" pageNumber="540">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stocchino" authorityYear="2018" box="[199,397,468,492]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Dugesiidae" genus="Dugesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tricladida" pageId="1" pageNumber="540" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="benazzii">
<emphasis box="[199,397,468,492]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="540">Dugesia benazzii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is represented by sexual and mixed natural populations, the latter characterized by the coexistence of sexual and fissiparous individuals (see Stocchino &amp; Manconi 2013). This species has a haploid chromosome complement of n=8, which is the most common set of chromosomes among 
<emphasis box="[1187,1280,541,564]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="540">Dugesia</emphasis>
species, with several biotypes that can be distinguished by the ploidy level and by the 
<typeStatus box="[1012,1060,576,600]" pageId="1" pageNumber="540">type</typeStatus>
of development (amphimixis or gynogenesis): (1) diploid, amphimictic (2n = 16; n = 8); (2) triploid, amphimictic (3n = 24; n = 8); (3) triploid, gynogenetic synaptic (3n = 24; n = 8); (4) tetraploid, gynogenetic asynaptic (4n = 32; n = 8) (
<bibRefCitation author="Lepori, N. G." box="[1266,1432,647,672]" pageId="1" pageNumber="540" pagination="92 - 101" refId="ref7070" refString="Lepori, N. G. (1948 a) Mutazione esaploide in una planaria della Sardegna appartenente al gen. Dugesia. Caryologia, 1, 92 - 101." type="journal article" year="1948">Lepori, 1948a</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Benazzi, M. &amp; Benazzi Lentati, G." box="[151,528,684,709]" pageId="1" pageNumber="540" pagination="1 - 182" refId="ref5860" refString="Benazzi, M. &amp; Benazzi Lentati, G. (1976) Platyhelminthes. In: John, B. (Ed.), Animal cytogenetics. Vol. 1. Gebruder Borntraeger, Berlin-Stuttgart, pp. 1 - 182." type="book chapter" year="1976">Benazzi &amp; Benazzi Lentati, 1976</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Vacca, R. A. &amp; Casu, S. &amp; Pala, M." box="[541,744,684,708]" pageId="1" pageNumber="540" pagination="131 - 147" refId="ref9109" refString="Vacca, R. A., Casu, S. &amp; Pala, M. (1988) Popolamento planariologico dei fiumi del Nord Sardegna. I. I cariotipi delle planarie d'acqua dolce del gruppo Dugesia gonocephala (Turbellaria, Tricladida) presenti nel fiume Silis (Sassari). Bollettino della Societa Sarda di Scienze Naturali, 26, 131 - 147." type="journal article" year="1988">
Vacca 
<emphasis box="[615,664,684,708]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="540">et al</emphasis>
., 1988
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Vacca, R. A. &amp; Casu, S. &amp; Pala, M." box="[756,815,684,708]" pageId="1" pageNumber="540" pagination="59 - 73" refId="ref9175" refString="Vacca, R. A., Casu, S. &amp; Pala, M. (1993) Popolamento planariologico dei fiumi del Nord Sardegna. II. I cariotipi dei Tricladi d'acqua dolce rinvenuti nel bacino idrografico del fiume Coghinas. Bollettino della Societa Sarda di Scienze Naturali, 29, 59 - 73." type="journal article" year="1993">1993</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Pala, M. &amp; Casu, S. &amp; Stocchino, G. A." box="[827,1014,684,709]" pageId="1" pageNumber="540" pagination="113 - 119" refId="ref7880" refString="Pala, M., Casu, S. &amp; Stocchino, G. A. (1999) Karyology and karyotype analysis of diploid freshwater planarian populations of the Dugesia gonocephala group (Platyhelminthes, Tricladida) found in Sardinia. Hydrobiologia, 392, 113 - 119. https: // doi. org / 10.1023 / A: 1003534507632" type="journal article" year="1999">
Pala 
<emphasis box="[883,932,684,708]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="540">et al</emphasis>
., 1999
</bibRefCitation>
). Moreover, a tetraploid, gynogenetic synaptic karyoptype (4n = 32; n = 8) and a hexaploid karyotype (6n = 48; n = 8) in a sexual population were also found in 
<collectingRegion box="[252,345,756,781]" country="Italy" name="Sardegna" pageId="1" pageNumber="540">Sardinia</collectingRegion>
(M. Pala, pers. comm.); the 
<typeStatus box="[666,714,757,781]" pageId="1" pageNumber="540">type</typeStatus>
of development of this last population is unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,359,997]" pageId="1" pageNumber="540">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stocchino" authorityYear="2018" box="[199,397,792,816]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Dugesiidae" genus="Dugesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tricladida" pageId="1" pageNumber="540" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="benazzii">
<emphasis box="[199,397,792,816]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="540">Dugesia benazzii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is widely distributed in 
<collectingRegion box="[696,789,791,816]" country="Italy" name="Sardegna" pageId="1" pageNumber="540">Sardinia</collectingRegion>
both in small rivers and in large hydrographic basins (
<bibRefCitation author="Lepori, N. G." box="[158,309,828,853]" pageId="1" pageNumber="540" pagination="28 - 47" refId="ref7174" refString="Lepori, N. G. (1951) Sulle caratteristiche morfologiche e sulla posizione sistematica della planaria di Sardegna e Corsica gia ascritta a Dugesia gonocephala (Duges). Atti Societa Toscana di Scienze Naturali, 58, 28 - 47." type="journal article" year="1951">Lepori, 1951</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Benazzi, M. &amp; Deri, P." box="[321,573,828,853]" pageId="1" pageNumber="540" pagination="45 - 54" refId="ref5904" refString="Benazzi, M. &amp; Deri, P. (1988) Taxonomic perspectives concerning fissiparous populations of the planarian Dugesia gonocephala s. l. inferred from ex-fissiparous specimens. Atti della Accademia Nazionale dei Lincei, 19, 45 - 54." type="journal article" year="1988">Benazzi &amp; Deri, 1988</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Vacca, R. A. &amp; Casu, S. &amp; Pala, M." box="[586,791,828,852]" pageId="1" pageNumber="540" pagination="131 - 147" refId="ref9109" refString="Vacca, R. A., Casu, S. &amp; Pala, M. (1988) Popolamento planariologico dei fiumi del Nord Sardegna. I. I cariotipi delle planarie d'acqua dolce del gruppo Dugesia gonocephala (Turbellaria, Tricladida) presenti nel fiume Silis (Sassari). Bollettino della Societa Sarda di Scienze Naturali, 26, 131 - 147." type="journal article" year="1988">
Vacca 
<emphasis box="[660,710,828,852]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="540">et al</emphasis>
., 1988
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Vacca, R. A. &amp; Casu, S. &amp; Pala, M." box="[804,863,828,852]" pageId="1" pageNumber="540" pagination="59 - 73" refId="ref9175" refString="Vacca, R. A., Casu, S. &amp; Pala, M. (1993) Popolamento planariologico dei fiumi del Nord Sardegna. II. I cariotipi dei Tricladi d'acqua dolce rinvenuti nel bacino idrografico del fiume Coghinas. Bollettino della Societa Sarda di Scienze Naturali, 29, 59 - 73." type="journal article" year="1993">1993</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Pala, M. &amp; Casu, S. &amp; Stocchino, G. A." box="[876,1063,828,853]" pageId="1" pageNumber="540" pagination="113 - 119" refId="ref7880" refString="Pala, M., Casu, S. &amp; Stocchino, G. A. (1999) Karyology and karyotype analysis of diploid freshwater planarian populations of the Dugesia gonocephala group (Platyhelminthes, Tricladida) found in Sardinia. Hydrobiologia, 392, 113 - 119. https: // doi. org / 10.1023 / A: 1003534507632" type="journal article" year="1999">
Pala 
<emphasis box="[932,982,828,852]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="540">et al</emphasis>
., 1999
</bibRefCitation>
; M. Pala, pers. comm.). A single population has been found also in a spring (Su Cantaru Spring) (
<bibRefCitation author="Stocchino, G. A. &amp; Sluys, R. &amp; Marcia, P. &amp; Manconi, R." box="[872,1132,863,888]" pageId="1" pageNumber="540" pagination="93 - 112" refId="ref8592" refString="Stocchino, G. A., Sluys, R., Marcia, P. &amp; Manconi, R. (2013 c) Subterranean aquatic planarians of Sardinia, with a discussion on the penial flagellum and the bursal canal sphincter in the genus Dendrocoelum (Platyhelminthes, Tricladida, Dendrocoelidae). Journal of Cave and Karst Studies, 75, 93 - 112. https: // doi. org / 10.4311 / 2011 LSC 0252" type="journal article" year="2013">
Stocchino 
<emphasis box="[992,1041,864,888]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="540">et al</emphasis>
., 2013c
</bibRefCitation>
) (
<figureCitation box="[1155,1220,863,888]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1435,1457]" captionTargetBox="[517,1104,299,1415]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[414,1176,277,1422]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Geographic distribution of species of the genus Dugesia recorded from Sardinia. 1, Rio d’Auteri reservoir, Asinara Island National Park; 2, Rio Mannu di Portotorres; 3, Fiume Silis; 4, Rio Lu Bagnu; 5, Fiume Coghinas; 6, Fiume Liscia; 7, spring and wells on the Tavolara Island Protected Area; 8, springs and unnamed rivulets on the Molara Island Protected Area; 9, Rio Su Lernu; 10, Rio Cuga; 11, Rio de sa Pazzosa; 12, Rio Torre Argentina; 13, Fiume Temo; 14, Sa Ucca ‘e su Peltusu Cave; 15, Rio S’Abba Mala; 16, Rio Mannu di Scano di Montiferro; 17, Rio Santa Caterina; 18, Fiume Tirso; 19, Su Cantaru Spring, Rio di Siniscola basin; 20, Fiume Cedrino; 21, Rio Osalla; 22, Rio Mannu di Milis; 23, Rio di Monte Arci; 24, Fiume Flumendosa; 25, Rio Mannu di Cagliari; 26, Fiume Quirra; 27, Rio Acqua ‘e sa Murta, S. Antioco Island; 28, Rio Triga, S. Antioco Island; 29, Rio ‘e sa Canna, S. Antioco Island; 30, Rio Flumentepido; 31, Rio Gutturu Mannu; 32, Rio Geremeas. New records are indicated by asterisks." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2615651/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="540">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,359,997]" pageId="1" pageNumber="540">
Until the 1960s 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stocchino" authorityYear="2018" box="[386,514,900,924]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Dugesiidae" genus="Dugesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tricladida" pageId="1" pageNumber="540" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="benazzii">
<emphasis box="[386,514,900,924]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="540">D. benazzii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was considered to be the only species of the genus 
<emphasis box="[1118,1211,901,924]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="540">Dugesia</emphasis>
present in 
<collectingRegion box="[1342,1435,900,925]" country="Italy" name="Sardegna" pageId="1" pageNumber="540">Sardinia</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Benazzi, M." box="[159,329,935,960]" pageId="1" pageNumber="540" pagination="153 - 159" refId="ref5763" refString="Benazzi, M. (1969) Nuovi reperti planariologici in isole tirreniche. Archivio Botanico e Biogeografico Italiano, 45, 153 - 159." type="journal article" year="1969">Benazzi, 1969</bibRefCitation>
). However, researches carried out by Lepori, Pala and co-workers since the 1970s led to the discovery of four other species, while in-depth investigations on their biology were also performed (see below).
</paragraph>
